This paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for machine learning applications, specifically for predicting spatiotemporal dynamical systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the optimization of key parameters in the neural network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reservoir computing systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of nonlinear partial differential equations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the design of optimal reservoir computing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
